<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00712</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT SPECIFYING THE REQUIREMENTS OF LEGITIMATE CONTRACTING/SUBCONTRACTING AMENDING FOR THIS PUPROSE ARTICLES 106 TO 109 OF PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES, AS AMENDED, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes the following: 1) Clearly defining legitimate contractor or subcontractor as an employer engaged in providing job, work or services to another business; 2) recognizing industry peculiarities through industry tripartite-determined functions or standards, application of the general standards on contracting and subcontracting; 3) in the absence of industry-tripartite standards, application of the general standards as determined by the Department of Labor and Employment (DOLE) Secretary, after consultation with the Tripartite Industrial Peace Council (TIPC); 4) prohibiting labor-only contracting; 5) licensing of contractors and subcontractors; 6) mandatory posting of bond to answer for the same; 7) coverage of the cooperatives as employers in contracting or subcontracting; and 8) reiteration of solidary liability in case of a finding of labor-only contracting.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ANGARA-CASTILLO, BELLAFLOR J.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Welfare</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06908</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2016-07-27</td></tr></table>